506
00:25:44.835 --> 00:25:46.521
Damn it. your students are dying!

507
00:25:46.545 --> 00:25:48.148
It was a terrible accident!

508
00:25:48.172 --> 00:25:49.798
It has no relevance here!

509
00:25:52.259 --> 00:25:55.530
Bixby says Barry has nothing
to do with these deaths.

510
00:25:55.554 --> 00:25:56.781
What do you think?

511
00:25:56.805 --> 00:25:58.575
I think we need to ask Barry.

512
00:26:00.309 --> 00:26:03.479
- Like a séance?
- Close.

513
00:26:04.229 --> 00:26:05.606
We're gonna exhume his body.

514
00:26:11.361 --> 00:26:12.422
Come in.

515
00:26:12.446 --> 00:26:14.174
Hey. will. Hey...

516
00:26:14.198 --> 00:26:16.259
hey. do me a favor and brace your core.

517
00:26:16.283 --> 00:26:20.138
I see so many herniated discs
from battles lost to Ikea's lagkapten.

518
00:26:21.663 --> 00:26:23.933
- Okay. Hello.
- Yeah.

519
00:26:23.957 --> 00:26:26.436
Angie. I think. is down at apd.

520
00:26:26.460 --> 00:26:29.647
No. I just saw her. We
just had lunch. I actually…

521
00:26:29.671 --> 00:26:31.024
I came up to see you.

522
00:26:31.048 --> 00:26:33.634
Can I give you a hand with that?

523
00:26:36.428 --> 00:26:38.323
You know. if you don't
mind. I lost my cuff link.

524
00:26:38.347 --> 00:26:40.147
- It's gotta be in here somewhere. So…
- sure.

525
00:26:40.641 --> 00:26:42.285
- Yeah. Yeah.
- You just wanna go out?

526
00:26:42.309 --> 00:26:43.787
- Here we go.
- One. two. three. go.

527
00:26:45.395 --> 00:26:47.373
So. you wanted to see me?

528
00:26:47.397 --> 00:26:49.250
Right. yeah. There's this…

529
00:26:49.274 --> 00:26:51.127
There's this guest
lecture coming up at gau.

530
00:26:51.151 --> 00:26:53.296
It's all about human parasites.

531
00:26:53.320 --> 00:26:54.738
I thought you might be interested.

532
00:26:56.740 --> 00:26:59.743
Why. yes. You know. I… I
would find that interesting. …

533
00:27:03.664 --> 00:27:05.874
- I don't see it back there.
- No. not this side either.

534
00:27:06.375 --> 00:27:07.519
Okay. let's go back.

535
00:27:07.543 --> 00:27:08.544
- Yep.
- Yep.

536
00:27:09.128 --> 00:27:11.773
You know. Angie and I
went to this baby class.

537
00:27:11.797 --> 00:27:13.149
I don't know if she told you.

538
00:27:13.173 --> 00:27:14.901
But it kind of freaked me out.

539
00:27:14.925 --> 00:27:18.554
Made me wanna really shore up
the village around this kid. you know?

540
00:27:19.513 --> 00:27:20.931
Sure.

541
00:27:22.349 --> 00:27:23.952
My family. they're all up north.

542
00:27:23.976 --> 00:27:26.454
and Angie's family is. you know. you.

543
00:27:26.478 --> 00:27:29.499
So. I thought it might be good if we…

544
00:27:29.523 --> 00:27:30.899
If we became friends.

545
00:27:33.193 --> 00:27:35.797
Aren't we sort of already friends?

546
00:27:35.821 --> 00:27:39.300
Yeah. I guess in a
non-friends friends kind of way.

547
00:27:39.324 --> 00:27:40.659
Will?

548
00:27:42.035 --> 00:27:44.121
- Hey. Seth.
- Hey.

549
00:27:44.955 --> 00:27:48.226
- What are you guys doing?
- We're looking for will's cuff link.

550
00:27:48.250 --> 00:27:49.978
You finish the exhumation autopsy?

551
00:27:50.002 --> 00:27:51.336
Yeah. I got it ready for you.

552
00:27:51.879 --> 00:27:55.215
Hey. Look at this. I found it.

553
00:27:55.966 --> 00:27:57.426
Did you say exhumation?

554
00:27:58.510 --> 00:27:59.761
Thank you.

555
00:28:01.763 --> 00:28:02.973
You got a few minutes?

556
00:28:06.018 --> 00:28:08.204
Well. it's gooier than I was expecting.

557
00:28:08.228 --> 00:28:09.539
I envisioned the mummy.

558
00:28:09.563 --> 00:28:11.541
- That's a great movie.
- Very underrated.

559
00:28:11.565 --> 00:28:13.358
I think the sequel is superior.

560
00:28:15.944 --> 00:28:18.756
Darkened tissue that persists
after a year of decomposition.

561
00:28:18.780 --> 00:28:20.365
Thoughts. gentlemen?

562
00:28:21.074 --> 00:28:22.594
All right. Pete.

563
00:28:22.618 --> 00:28:24.369
- Frostbite?
- Correct.

564
00:28:25.245 --> 00:28:28.933
Small hemorrhages in the
stomach and pancreatic lining

565
00:28:28.957 --> 00:28:31.644
- known as wischnewski spots.
- Hypothermia. right?

566
00:28:31.668 --> 00:28:34.230
One point to Dr. Seth.
though you had the edge there.

567
00:28:34.254 --> 00:28:35.481
Whoa. are there points?

568
00:28:35.505 --> 00:28:38.216
Not a competition. but it is also a tie.

569
00:28:39.217 --> 00:28:41.946
Moving along. Splinters
found embedded in his feet

570
00:28:41.970 --> 00:28:44.490
from hickory. black
locust. and cedar trees.

571
00:28:44.514 --> 00:28:47.952
Sounds like he was walking barefoot
in the forest. That's another point. right?

572
00:28:47.976 --> 00:28:51.331
Yet the responding officers
noted he was found fully dressed.

573
00:28:51.355 --> 00:28:54.083
Speaking of clothing. Pete.
what was the victim buried in?

574
00:28:54.107 --> 00:28:56.526
Suit's there. I haven't examined it yet.

575
00:28:57.069 --> 00:28:59.422
- Ready for the next finding?
- Yeah. bring it on.

576
00:28:59.446 --> 00:29:02.133
Trace amounts of adhesive
found in the tissue lining

577
00:29:02.157 --> 00:29:04.510
of his inner lips. teeth
and tip of his tongue.

578
00:29:04.534 --> 00:29:06.387
- His mouth was taped shut?
- Yep.

579
00:29:06.411 --> 00:29:10.183
And lastly. gold flakes
found in his stomach.

580
00:29:10.207 --> 00:29:11.351
Goldenkränz.

581
00:29:11.375 --> 00:29:12.936
- Correct.
- Hey.

582
00:29:12.960 --> 00:29:15.396
Hey. Dr. Seth is really
running away with this. will.

583
00:29:15.420 --> 00:29:16.648
I'm sorry.

584
00:29:16.672 --> 00:29:19.508
This young man was murdered.
I'm not engaging in a competition.

585
00:29:20.175 --> 00:29:21.653
Because you're losing.

586
00:29:21.677 --> 00:29:22.737
That's correct.

587
00:29:22.761 --> 00:29:24.822
Well. whatever
happened to this poor kid.

588
00:29:24.846 --> 00:29:27.533
the official story does not
match the evidence on the body.

589
00:29:27.557 --> 00:29:29.452
Because Barry probably
died in his underwear

590
00:29:29.476 --> 00:29:31.454
just like our present-day victims.

591
00:29:31.478 --> 00:29:34.832
Someone later dressed
him. left him to be found.

592
00:29:34.856 --> 00:29:36.960
Whoever killed Paxton and sharkey.

593
00:29:36.984 --> 00:29:38.944
they know the truth about Barry's death.

594
00:29:41.071 --> 00:29:42.864
Maybe even helped cover it up.

595
00:29:47.285 --> 00:29:50.181
This is a note that will
found in Barry's burial suit.

596
00:29:50.205 --> 00:29:52.350
presumably tucked in
by someone at the funeral.

597
00:29:52.374 --> 00:29:54.310
"I will never forget."

598
00:29:54.334 --> 00:29:59.232
And this is a photo that
Angie took of brit's handwriting.

599
00:29:59.256 --> 00:30:03.820
Words on the duct tape were all caps.
so we couldn't match them conclusively.

600
00:30:03.844 --> 00:30:05.947
But these two samples. they match.

601
00:30:05.971 --> 00:30:08.658
I was able to track down
the filing of brit's nda.

602
00:30:08.682 --> 00:30:11.452
and I'm still trying to get
access to specific details.

603
00:30:11.476 --> 00:30:14.914
but it was filed the
day after Barry's death.

604
00:30:14.938 --> 00:30:17.417
So the damn nda was
never about the sex tape.

605
00:30:17.441 --> 00:30:18.501
It was about Barry.

606
00:30:18.525 --> 00:30:20.294
I've been doing this a while.

607
00:30:20.318 --> 00:30:22.714
A million bucks says the
sex tape was a diversion.

608
00:30:22.738 --> 00:30:25.800
Barry dies. they leak the sex tape.

609
00:30:25.824 --> 00:30:27.909
Suddenly. no one's talking about Barry.

610
00:30:29.703 --> 00:30:31.806
What if brit was dating Paxton.

611
00:30:31.830 --> 00:30:33.874
but also had a secret
relationship with Barry?

612
00:30:34.833 --> 00:30:37.586
Paxton found out. led to
Barry's death by hazing.

613
00:30:38.211 --> 00:30:39.981
The guilt got to be too much.

614
00:30:40.005 --> 00:30:41.232
She finally snapped.

615
00:30:41.256 --> 00:30:42.966
Secrets will do that to you.

616
00:30:43.884 --> 00:30:45.987
Now she's exacting revenge.

617
00:30:46.011 --> 00:30:47.572
Anyone involved could be in danger.

618
00:30:47.596 --> 00:30:49.449
If Paxton and sharkey
were there that night.

619
00:30:49.473 --> 00:30:50.700
then so were badger and Sean.

620
00:30:50.724 --> 00:30:51.909
Those four were inseparable.

621
00:30:51.933 --> 00:30:55.705
Go. Get Sean. chancellor
Bixby and this Wolverine.

622
00:30:55.729 --> 00:30:57.206
- Badger.
- Whatever.

623
00:30:57.230 --> 00:30:58.916
Put them in protective custody.

624
00:30:58.940 --> 00:31:02.170
And we'll deal with whatever
they did to Barry once this is done.

625
00:31:02.194 --> 00:31:05.280
And find brit before
she kills somebody else.

626
00:31:15.832 --> 00:31:17.310
- Hey. toothbrush.
- Hey.

627
00:31:17.334 --> 00:31:18.752
Where's Sean and badger?

628
00:31:19.544 --> 00:31:21.939
I haven't seen 'em. but
they're probably at the quad.

629
00:31:21.963 --> 00:31:24.275
There's a memorial
for Paxton and sharkey.

630
00:31:24.299 --> 00:31:25.610
All the houses are going.

631
00:31:25.634 --> 00:31:27.794
Why do you still have the
toothbrush? It's disgusting.

632
00:31:28.678 --> 00:31:29.846
Commitment.

633
00:31:30.847 --> 00:31:33.367
Okay. Let's split up.

634
00:31:33.391 --> 00:31:36.037
I'll go to the quad. you sweep the
house. make sure they're not there.

635
00:31:36.061 --> 00:31:37.997
No. I'll go to the quad. I'm taller.

636
00:31:38.021 --> 00:31:41.584
Hopefully. I can spot these two
in a sea of Zack. Jakes and Joshs.

637
00:31:41.608 --> 00:31:43.836
- All right. sounds good.
- All right.

638
00:31:53.245 --> 00:31:54.472
Hey. Georgia.

639
00:31:54.496 --> 00:31:56.891
Georgia. we're looking
for brit. Have you seen her?

640
00:31:56.915 --> 00:31:59.769
Like an hour ago. She was
headed towards the woods.

641
00:31:59.793 --> 00:32:01.270
The same woods
where Barry was found?

642
00:32:01.294 --> 00:32:03.797
- I think so.
- Hopefully we're not too late.

643
00:32:20.397 --> 00:32:23.358
Apd. Anybody here?

644
00:32:26.111 --> 00:32:27.237
Sean?

645
00:32:29.656 --> 00:32:30.740
Badger?

646
00:32:32.033 --> 00:32:33.636
Clear!

647
00:32:33.660 --> 00:32:35.495
Let's get a light on this tree line!

648
00:32:36.121 --> 00:32:37.164
Brit!

649
00:32:37.831 --> 00:32:41.519
It's gbi special agent Mitchell.
We know you're out here.

650
00:32:41.543 --> 00:32:42.836
Badger!

651
00:33:20.749 --> 00:33:22.417
Baby girl.

652
00:33:24.252 --> 00:33:27.231
Somehow. your momma
is still not used to this belly.

653
00:33:27.255 --> 00:33:30.884
even though it feels like I've
been pregnant with you for a year.

654
00:33:41.436 --> 00:33:42.747
Brit.

655
00:33:44.064 --> 00:33:45.208
Badger.

656
00:33:48.526 --> 00:33:50.421
Brit!

657
00:33:50.445 --> 00:33:51.529
Sean!

658
00:33:55.784 --> 00:33:57.911
Ormewood! Mitchell!

659
00:33:59.204 --> 00:34:01.349
Come over here!

660
00:34:04.834 --> 00:34:06.145
She's alive.

661
00:34:16.388 --> 00:34:17.973
Is that Barry?

662
00:34:24.604 --> 00:34:25.981
Sean.

663
00:34:26.648 --> 00:34:29.985
God. Sean.

664
00:34:37.742 --> 00:34:39.452
This is detective Polaski.

665
00:34:40.120 --> 00:34:42.682
I'm at the delta kappa chi
house on the gau campus.

666
00:34:42.706 --> 00:34:43.975
I need immediate backup.

667
00:34:43.999 --> 00:34:47.770
and alert special agents Mitchell
and Trent that the killer is Sean Bixby.

668
00:35:08.607 --> 00:35:09.649
Sean.

669
00:35:13.612 --> 00:35:14.714
Let's not do this.

670
00:35:14.738 --> 00:35:16.031
You should go.

671
00:35:16.573 --> 00:35:17.842
I'm burning it all down.

672
00:35:17.866 --> 00:35:18.867
Because of Barry.

673
00:35:19.534 --> 00:35:20.803
No. you don't understand.

674
00:35:20.827 --> 00:35:22.412
I know you cared about him.

675
00:35:23.204 --> 00:35:24.247
Cared?

676
00:35:27.709 --> 00:35:28.877
No. I loved him.

677
00:35:29.502 --> 00:35:31.004
Then I couldn't even say his name.

678
00:35:32.005 --> 00:35:33.816
No one would even talk
about what happened.

679
00:35:33.840 --> 00:35:35.592
So let's talk about it.

680
00:35:36.092 --> 00:35:37.761
Tell me what happened the night he died.

681
00:35:39.137 --> 00:35:40.513
I'm listening.

682
00:35:41.097 --> 00:35:43.600
I… I should've stopped him.

683
00:35:45.393 --> 00:35:47.354
It was the night of the gatsby party.

684
00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:50.982
Barry was drunk and
spilled his drink on me.

685
00:35:53.026 --> 00:35:54.795
I was such a bitch.

686
00:35:56.112 --> 00:35:58.073
I told Paxton he needed to pay.

687
00:36:00.492 --> 00:36:03.095
It was just supposed to be a
pledge walk through campus.

688
00:36:03.119 --> 00:36:05.455
But Paxton and sharkey kept piling on.

689
00:36:06.247 --> 00:36:07.874
until Barry was naked.

690
00:36:08.667 --> 00:36:10.978
in the woods. drunk. soaking wet.

691
00:36:11.002 --> 00:36:13.755
saying he was sorry over and over.

692
00:36:15.090 --> 00:36:19.511
And that's when badger…
…taped his mouth shut.

693
00:36:20.553 --> 00:36:23.324
Because pledges don't
speak. Isn't that right. badger?

694
00:36:24.683 --> 00:36:26.726
And we left him there
to find his way back.

695
00:36:29.020 --> 00:36:30.289
I left him there.

696
00:36:30.313 --> 00:36:33.024
He never came home.

697
00:36:33.650 --> 00:36:39.280
So. the next morning.
we all went looking for him.

698
00:36:39.864 --> 00:36:42.259
And he was still in the woods.

699
00:36:42.283 --> 00:36:48.248
and he had covered himself with
leaves and branches to stay warm.

700
00:36:48.957 --> 00:36:50.959
He looked so small and pale.

701
00:36:51.960 --> 00:36:53.169
He was dead.

702
00:36:55.046 --> 00:36:56.941
Why didn't I stop them?

703
00:36:56.965 --> 00:36:59.926
I know you want to stop them
now. but it won't bring him back.

704
00:37:01.386 --> 00:37:03.197
This isn't what Barry would want for you.

705
00:37:03.221 --> 00:37:05.348
Do you know what Barry would want?

706
00:37:06.975 --> 00:37:09.328
To not die alone in the woods.

707
00:37:09.352 --> 00:37:10.937
Sean called his dad.

708
00:37:11.980 --> 00:37:13.106
Chancellor Bixby.

709
00:37:14.023 --> 00:37:18.194
And. he told us to just put
clothes on Barry and leave.

710
00:37:19.571 --> 00:37:22.031
The next day a lawyer
showed up with an nda.

711
00:37:24.242 --> 00:37:26.161
I didn't mean for him to die.

712
00:37:27.287 --> 00:37:28.889
I'm so sorry.

713
00:37:33.251 --> 00:37:35.545
My father said we just have to move on.

714
00:37:37.297 --> 00:37:39.299
Like Barry never existed.

715
00:37:41.259 --> 00:37:43.553
To protect our futures.

716
00:37:44.637 --> 00:37:46.556
He said that was all that mattered.

717
00:37:48.641 --> 00:37:50.286
But Barry mattered.

718
00:37:50.310 --> 00:37:51.620
I know he did.

719
00:37:51.644 --> 00:37:52.771
Stay back.

720
00:37:53.897 --> 00:37:55.523
Please just get out of here.

721
00:37:56.649 --> 00:37:58.151
I'm not going to do that. Sean.

722
00:37:59.402 --> 00:38:00.570
I'm here with you.

723
00:38:01.529 --> 00:38:03.299
We can break the cycle. you and me.

724
00:38:03.323 --> 00:38:05.593
Hey. look at me.

725
00:38:05.617 --> 00:38:06.701
Sean…

726
00:38:08.036 --> 00:38:09.513
Don't do this to us.

727
00:38:21.966 --> 00:38:26.346
Sean Bixby. you're under arrest for the
murders of Paxton Cole and Greg sharkens.

728
00:38:34.354 --> 00:38:35.563
Did you find the killer?

729
00:38:36.147 --> 00:38:38.066
How's my son? Is he safe?

730
00:38:38.858 --> 00:38:40.211
We have the killer in custody.

731
00:38:41.986 --> 00:38:43.947
And my son. can I see him?

732
00:38:44.614 --> 00:38:45.782
As I said.

733
00:38:46.324 --> 00:38:48.201
we have the killer in custody.

734
00:38:50.495 --> 00:38:51.496
No.

735
00:38:53.623 --> 00:38:57.770
No. that's… that's not possible. I
need to speak to Sean. Talk to him.

736
00:38:57.794 --> 00:39:00.755
He has requested that the
two of you don't have contact.

737
00:39:01.297 --> 00:39:03.234
He'll be seeking his own legal counsel.

738
00:39:03.258 --> 00:39:05.027
I suggest you reach out to yours.

739
00:39:05.051 --> 00:39:06.987
Wait. I… what?

740
00:39:07.011 --> 00:39:11.450
You're facing charges of conspiracy.
obstruction. and child endangerment

741
00:39:11.474 --> 00:39:14.286
for orchestrating the
cover-up of Barry evers's death.

742
00:39:14.310 --> 00:39:15.687
But Sean…

743
00:39:17.105 --> 00:39:18.874
Why… why would he?

744
00:39:18.898 --> 00:39:21.860
You did everything to protect
the future you wanted for Sean.

745
00:39:22.902 --> 00:39:25.572
You never stopped to ask if
it was the future he wanted.

746
00:39:41.546 --> 00:39:43.774
Hey. I'm about to call
Barry evers's family.

747
00:39:43.798 --> 00:39:45.359
What's the da got to say?

748
00:39:45.383 --> 00:39:47.152
They're going for
manslaughter for badger.

749
00:39:47.176 --> 00:39:48.237
And the girl?

750
00:39:48.261 --> 00:39:50.823
She's helping out with the
case against the chancellor.

751
00:39:50.847 --> 00:39:55.411
Turns out that he helped cover up
dozens of crimes committed by that frat.

752
00:39:55.435 --> 00:39:57.830
which. by the way. is losing their charter.

753
00:39:57.854 --> 00:40:00.875
And to think a pair of secret
lovers could cause so much tragedy.

754
00:40:00.899 --> 00:40:03.109
You're only as sick as your secrets.

755
00:40:10.533 --> 00:40:11.719
You want to talk about it?

756
00:40:11.743 --> 00:40:12.785
No.

757
00:40:15.872 --> 00:40:17.040
I look at you.

758
00:40:17.707 --> 00:40:21.920
and the career you've
had. and what it's cost.

